post_text: If you were not at the Highmark game last night‚Ä¶you missed the game of the year. Special thanks to all the fans and the cheerleaders for coming out and being so loud and for cheering us on. The Hawks had a rough start being down 12-2 after the first but fought back and were down 14-7 at half. The Hawks then exploded in the 3rd for 15 points and were down one going into the 4th. The Hawks and Rams battled the entire 4th with the lead changing side constantly, sadly the Rams would hit some big free throws to close out the game and would come away with the win 35-31. The Hawks gave everything last night and the coaches could not be more proud of them The Hawks were led by 9th grader Jenika W who went Lebron on the Rams driving into contact constantly and finishing at the rim and finished with 17 points. Savanna P had her first 3 pointer ever that made the crowd erupt into a frenzy. The combined defense of Emma W and Kora L intimated their opponents the whole night. The Hawks play their final game of the season tomorrow at Mound Fort. Go Hawks

post_text: The Hawks thought it be funny to make coach Jackson a little nervous at the start of the game last night by having a rough start being down 13-2. But they then showed why they are such an amazing team, they banded together and fought with everything they had to have a one point lead at the half. The Hawks then held the hikers scoreless in the 3rd quarter and would go on to win 44-37. The Hawks had a season and career high from Jenika who had 24 points along with Savanna adding 9 and Emma using her length to disrupt the hikers in the second half as well. The Hawks play our rivals tomorrow at 3:30 against the Mount Ogden Rams. Come out and support. Go Hawks.

post_text: Our 1st graders were practicing ‚ÄúWin-Win‚Äù in PE. The kids had to work together as teams and and a whole grade to get all the balls in the baskets. Some were holding the baskets, some were drivers and some had pool noodles to push the ball to the basket...no hands allowed. At first they were fighting over the balls, but then we discussed think win-win and how they could work together better to lower their time to get all the balls. It worked really well!

post_text:
Dear Parents,
As you know, the National Weather Service has issued a winter warning from tonight at 10:00 PM to Monday at 10:00 PM. Forecasts call for 4-8 inches with up to 14 inches on the benches with concerns of winds. Travel could be dangerous.
Due to that warning, HighMark will join with Davis District in conducting a two our late start.
This means that school will start at 10:20 AM. AM kindergarten will be cancelled. PM kindergarten will be at the usual time.
In the event that the weather worsens, the decision to cancel school entirely will be made by 6:30 AM Monday.
To reiterate , we will hold school tomorrow, just two hours later than the normal start time.
Be safe!

post_text: We had the honor of having Sam Bracken, author of My Orange Duffel Bag: A Journey to Radical Change come talk to our Jr. High today. He was homeless at 15. Sam managed to overcome incredible obstacles, graduate #11 out of 700 students from his Las Vegas high school and landed a full-ride football scholarship to Georgia Tech. He arrived at Georgia Tech with everything he owned in an orange duffel bag. Sam is now married with 4 children, serves as the VP of Business Development for Garff Enterprises, has founded the Orange Duffel Bag initiative and taught HMCS students today that they always have a choice, can map their own future, choose better over bitter, and to see those around them who are helping them achieve their best selves while they never give up working for it.

post_text:
Hi parents,

We are going to make a couple of changes to our carpool system in the afternoon for pick-ups. We are doing these changes because the safety of our students is our number one priority.

1 - The teacher on the west side of the building will now become the traffic director! This person will have a stop sign and an orange vest. This person will be responsible for directing one car at a time to turn into the lane where students are picked up closest to the building.

2- Once you are directed to turn, please pull forward as far east as you can towards the flag pole.

3 - East of the flag pole will now be a dedicated loading zone for commercial vans who pick children up. Once the vans arrive, they will park in the loading zone. This zone will be marked off with orange cones. Please do not park in the van loading zone. You will need to go around the vans as you exit the carpool lane.

post_text: The Hawks played one of the best games I have ever seen last night against the Mount Ogden Rams. The Hawks played tough being down 2 after the first but would be down by only 8 at half thanks to a huge 3 pointer from Madi Smith but would be down by as many as 14 in the 4th. But while the Rams and many fans thought the game was over the Hawks continued to believe and trust in their team. The Hawks came storming back, I'm talking like a hurricane storm to tie the score at 33 all thanks to 2 huge free throws from Abby Petersen. The gym was litterally shaking with 1 minute left from excitement for the Hawks but sadly before the come back could be complete the buzzer rang out. The final score being 38-34. The Hawks had 11 points from Sarah Mower and 6 from Faith Petersen. The team was able to make the come back thanks to the awesome defense of Jack, Georgia, D money and Bree. Thanks to all who came out to support us and to the girls thanks for the best season and for giving it your all last night. Go Hawks

post_text: Well the Hawks decided it would be fun on Friday to give themselves, the fans and their coaches a small heart attack. The Hawks pulled out a nail biter on Friday defeating the Syracuse Dragons 52-51. The Hawks were down 8 in the 4th quarter and needed to score 21 points in the final quarter to pull out the win. The Hawks gave everything they had and hit some huge free throws down the stretch to seal the win including the final two from Faith P. The Hawks were led by Abby P who had 19 points and 23 rebounds and Faith P who had 17 points. The Hawks have a road game today at Highland. Go Hawks.

post_text: What a game, what a game... Did I mention what a game last night the Hawks played against the Quest Academy Rams. The Hawks played their best basketball of the season against a really good Rams team. The Hawks and Rams battle back and forth just like in nature all the way to the forth quarter with the Hawks always holding a small lead. The Hawks were up 1 with about a minute left in the game when Faith P got fouled and went to the line and sunk two huge free throws to ice the game. The Hawks played team ball the entire time. They where led by Sarah M who had 15 points and Faith Petersen who added 12. The Hawks were able to outrebound the Rams thanks to D Money and Abby P who had 10 and 9 rebounds respectfully. The Hawks play the Mount Ogden Rams on Wednesday here at Highmark at 4:30 Go Hawks.

post_text: The Hawks played their last game of the season on Friday against the Syrcause Arts Dragons. The Hawks came out to a rough start going down by 10 points early. In the 4th quarter the Hawks mounted a strong comeback but simply ran out of time. The Hawks finished the season in 3rd place with a 10-4 record. The B team did finish their season undefeated! Coach Scov and Jackson want to thank all the student and teachers who came out to support us this year. And to the boys on the team thank you for letting us be your coaches this year and for giving your best each and every day. You made the school, coaches and fans very proud.

post_text: The Hawks came away with a huge win last night to kick off their new season and they also got Scov to wear a shirt and tie to look more intimidating since he wanted to dress up for the game. The Hawks have their first home game this Friday at 3:30 against UMA make sure to come out and support! Go Hawks!

Today we welcomed Hill Air Force Base to HighMark. Grades K-3 spent their morning with military heroes, not only learning about their jobs, but also hearing them read.
Grades 4-6 got to watch a presentation by the Explosive Ordinance Disposal Team from Hill Air Force Base. They dressed Mr. Pace in the bomb suit and demonstrated their robot.

post_text: The cross country team had their championship meet in the rain last Thursday. All of the girls improved on their times and did a great job. post_text: The Lady Hawks soccer team capped off their great season with a 3 game winning streak by defeating the highland hikers 6-1. The two teams were both dialed in and played a great defensive first half the hikers only allowed two goals one from Megan "shaggy" and the other from Georgia "Goldfish". In the second half the Hawks would leave it all on the field getting 4 more goals from Sara "stack attack" stackerak, Devery D money, Megan. The Hawks had amazing goalie play from Allie the Spiderman. The coaches would like the thank all the girls for an amazing season and for all the fans and cheerleaders for being at the games and supporting this season. Go Hawks.

post_text: Everything about the volleyball game yesterday made it feel like a championship game, and the Lady Hawks once again showed why they are your true champions. Faith and Tyler led the team in serving while Bree and Livy were pounding the ball down at the net. Coming from behind the hawks were able to win their last two sets and strip Mt Ogden from their undefeated title. Destined to meet each other once more in the championship game, these sisters know that the war with the Rams isn't over. But there is something about playing Mt Ogden that brings out our inner hawk! KA-KAAAAAAAAAAWWWWWWWWW!!!

post_text: The volleyball team put on an amazing clinic against Quest Academy yesterday winning all three of their matches. Faith and Tyler led the team in serving and Bree led the team in spikes. The fans were excited for the win, but the lady hawks seemed too focused on the goal ahead to share in the celebration. Only one team will satisfy their unquenchable thirst for Ram's blood, and it's not the Quest Academy Rams. This team has escaped the Hawk's wrath for long enough. So don't miss Wednesday's game when we hand Mt. Ogden their first loss.

The cross country team had two meets last week. On Tuesday the girls team was led by Elena C who finished 10th with a time of 19:31. Maliyah T also had a great race and turned in her best performance finishing 12th with a time of 19:50. The boys team finished 3rd on Tuesday and was led by Colton S and Kye J who both finished in the top 20. Colton finished with a time of 14:25 and Kye came in at 14:31.



On Thursday the girls were again led by Elena who turned in a great time of 16:21. For the boys Colton S finished 16th with a time of 13:31 and Vann W ran his best race so far finishing 21st with a time of 13:56. The cross country team has their next meet on Thursday.

post_text: The Highmark Hawks baseball team captured their second title in 4 years last night with a hard fought victory over the Syracuse Dragons 5-3. The Hawks finished the season on a eight game win streak after a bumpy 2-2 start. Jory continued his masterful season going the whole game for the Hawks. The defense also showed up big last night with great plays all over the field from Anthony, Boomer, Jayden, Landon, and Roman. The boys worked hard this season, and that work paid off last night. Miehlke and Scov are super proud of the effort, and work these guys put in this season. Also, with no 9th graders the whole team should be back and ready to defend the title next year!

post_text: The Highmark Hawks improved their record to 4-2 on the season with an easy 16-2 victory over the Mt. Ogden Rams last night. The Hawks walked around the bases a lot last night as Mt. Highmark will take on Syracuse next Tuesday at home.

post_text: The Highmark Hawks dropped to 2-2 on the season after losing to the Highland Hiker 3-1 last night. Jory pitched another great game for the Hawks only allowing one earned run. post_text: The Hawks got back on track with a terrific win yesterday against the Highland Hikers. The Hawks controlled the game from the start scoring in the first 5 minutes. The Hawks were led on offense by Dominic ‚ÄúI‚Äôm a Defender‚Äù who recorded the hat trick scoring all 3 goals, two of which were assisted on crosses by Jackson Bunn. The Hawks played amazing defense stopping numerous shots including several free kicks right outside the box, Carson M and the Defense recorded their second shutout of the season. The B team did a fantastic job controlling the ball majority of the game and winning 4-1. The Hawks had goals from Dom R who also added an amazing celebration, Brad J, Cameron G, and Parker B. The Hawks play tomorrow here at Highmark at 3:30 come out and support.

post_text: The Highmark Hawks suffered their first defeat of the season last night to Syracuse Arts 8-7. The Hawks jumped out to a 5-0 lead behind some good hitting, but let Syracuse come back and tie the game 5-5. Syracuse was able to put 3 more runs on the board in the 6th to make it a 8-5 game. The Hawks fought back, having the tying run on 2nd base but fell just short of the comeback. The Hawks dropped to 2-1 on the season and will look to bounce back against a tough Highland team on Wednesday.

post_text: The Hawks had a terrific start to the season defeating the Syracuse Arts Dragons 5-0. The Hawks were able to do this with great possession and team defense. The Hawks had 2 goals apiece from Ben M. and Jayden L. and also a terrific goal from Dominic C. The Hawks defense held the Dragons to only a handful of shots and Carson M. got his first shutout of the season. The B team also came away with a win 1-0 with the lone goal of the game coming from Colby S. and assisted by Dom R. The Hawks play on Friday against Mount Ogden here at home make sure to come out and support and bring a jacket since it‚Äôs supposed to be raining and that way you have no excuse for not coming.

post_text: The Lady Hawks finished a terrific season with a record of 10-2. The hawks came up just short last night against the Mount Ogden Rams. The Hawks were down 7 at half but they never stopped believing in themselves and their team. The hawks came out soaring in the 3rd quarter scoring a Highmark Girls basketball record of 20 points in a single quarter and would be up 3 going into the 4th. The hawks fought the entire final quarter but just couldn‚Äôt find the basket enough. Coach Jackson would like to thank all the amazing fans we had last night cheering on this amazing team. He also wants to remind the girls how proud he is of them and that they are all champions to him. Remember girls Heart and remember Ye Ye.

post_text: The Lady Hawks kept their season going last night with a huge win in the semifinals against the Syracuse Arts Dragons. The Hawks were only up 4 at half but came alive in the second half to finish the game with a score of 37-22. The Hawks were able to make the push with great defense and rebounding and also with the scoring effort of Sara S. who went old school NBA jam on fire scoring 12 points and Hope M. adding 6 and Abby P. adding 5. The Hawks host the championship tomorrow at home we want every student to come out tomorrow and support the girls. We are having a white out game so if you wear white tomorrow you don‚Äôt have to wear a collar. We need our home crowd to help cheer us on to victory. Thanks for all the fans who were there last night including the rumble squad.

post_text: The Lady Hawks picked up their first loss of the season to the Mount Ogden Rams in a close hard fought game last night. The Hawks led by 3 after the first quarter but were down 2 at half. The hawks would fall behind by ten in the 3rd but would make a dramatic comeback getting the game within 5 in the last minute but sadly would run out of time before they could finish off the amazing comeback. The Hawks were led by Faith P. who had 13 points and Hope M. who added 7. The Hawks played amazing defense in the second half to stage the comeback as well. The Hawks play tomorrow here against Syracuse so make sure to stay for the game and cheer them on. Go Hawks.

post_text: The ladyhawks had an exciting win on Friday against the Highland Hikers. The Hawks started off strong being up 10-0 after the first but stalled in the second and only led at half 12-11. The Ladyhawks would respond in the second half with terrific team defense and hustle. The Hawks were led by Sara S. who had 14 points and 6 points from Hope M. all in the 4th quarter to help the Hawks win the game 30-11. The B game was an exciting game with the Hawks pulling out a close win of 10-6 with 2 big shots from Micah S. and Gussie G. The Hawks play today at Mount Ogden make sure to wish all the girls good luck.
